org.sbml.jsbml.xml.stax

Class SBMLReader

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.sbml.jsbml.xml.stax.SBMLReader

  • public class SBMLReader
extends java.lang.Object
    Provides all the methods to read a SBML file.

    Warning: This class is not thread safe, so if using several thread to process SBML files in parallel you should make sure to use new instances of SBMLReader in each thread.

    Since:
    0.8
    Author:
    Marine Dumousseau, Andreas Dräger, Nicolas Rodriguez, Clemens Wrzodek

      • main

        public static void main(java.lang.String[] args)
                 throws java.io.IOException,
                        javax.xml.stream.XMLStreamException,
                        SBMLException
        Reads the file that is passed as argument and write it to the console, using the method SBMLWriter.write(SBMLDocument, java.io.OutputStream).
        Parameters:
        args - the command line arguments, we are taking the first one as the file name to read.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if the file name is not valid.
        SBMLException - if there are any problems reading or writing the SBML model.
        javax.xml.stream.XMLStreamException - if there are any problems reading or writing the XML file.
